{
  "texts": [
    "where the summation ranges over all pairs 〈ij〉 of neighboring sites on the lattice and the couplings {J ij } are sampled uniformly from the interval [0, 2].",
    "Here, the vector x is a of all couplings J ij so that the dimension of the parameter space is m = O(n), where n is the system size.",
    "The nonnegative interval [0, 2] corresponds to antiferromagnetic interactions.",
    "To minimize the Heisenberg interaction terms, nearby qubits have to form singlet states.",
    "While the square lattice is bipartite and lacks the standard geometric frustration, the presence of disorder makes the ground state calculation more challenging as neighboring qubits will compete in the formation of singlets due to the monogamy of entanglement 63."
  ]
}